## Common Demo Patterns

### MaaS API Testing
```bash
# Generate token
HOST="https://maas.${CLUSTER_DOMAIN}"
TOKEN_RESPONSE=$(curl -sSk \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $(oc whoami -t)" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -X POST \
  -d '{"expiration": "10m"}' \
  "${HOST}/maas-api/v1/tokens")
TOKEN=$(echo $TOKEN_RESPONSE | jq -r .token)

# List models
curl -sSk ${HOST}/maas-api/v1/models \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" | jq .

# Chat completion
curl -X POST "${HOST}/v1/chat/completions" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "my-model",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}]
  }'
```

### RHOAI 3.3+ MaaS Testing
```bash
# Generate token
TOKEN=$(oc create token default -n my-namespace --duration=1h)

# Call inference gateway
curl -X POST "https://inference-gateway.apps.${CLUSTER_DOMAIN}/v1/chat/completions" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "my-model",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}]
  }'
```

### Streamlit App Pattern
```python
import streamlit as st
import requests

# Get MaaS endpoint from environment
MAAS_ENDPOINT = os.getenv("MAAS_ENDPOINT", "https://inference-gateway.apps.cluster.example.com")

def chat_completion(model, messages, token):
    response = requests.post(
        f"{MAAS_ENDPOINT}/v1/chat/completions",
        headers={
            "Authorization": f"Bearer {token}",
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        },
        json={
            "model": model,
            "messages": messages
        }
    )
    return response.json()
```

